The U.S. military has deployed a new "smart" weapon in Afghanistan, known only as the XM-25.
The generals hope that the new automatic rifle will affect the conflict with the Taliban and "change the game" in their favor.
A new weapon is like a small super-precision gun.
Its projectiles are guided by a laser with an accuracy of several meters.
Special 25 mm rounds, developed for this rifle and containing a high-explosive explosive, actually work like small grenades.
The cartridges can be programmed to explode not only on impact with the target, but at any point in its ballistic path.
They can therefore be used against an enemy who is hiding behind an obstacle, behind a wall or in a trench.
