Early next year, the court will begin investigating Nuon Chea, Khieu Samphan, Ieng Sary and his wife, Ieng Thirith, another former Khmer Rouge minister.
The court has a mandate to prosecute senior officials and people responsible for the crimes, but it has not been said whether it will continue in the four cases.
It was little to calm the anxieties in Anlong Veng.
Recent media speculation centered on Im Chaema, 64, who was a district leader in Banteay Meanchey Province during the Khmer Rouge rule in the late 1970s.
