"There is peace in Cambodia and it is stable," she said.
"If there are more prosecutions, there will be war."
Prime Minister Hun Sen, who defected from the Khmer Rouge in 1978, has also repeatedly warned that there will be instability if the court searches for more suspects, although experts and historians disagree.
"Cambodia must dig a deep hole and bury the past in it," he said.
