"Reconciliation in Khmer terms means the bonding of broken pieces," he said.
"It's our duty to put these broken pieces together so we can understand each other."
The center has published the first textbook approved by the government on the Khmer Rouge, it has 75 pages and the title "History of Democratic Cambodia."
